257
00:19:28,540 --> 00:19:30,550
<i>Code zero. Hit-and-run vehicle
is fleeing the scene.</i>

258
00:19:30,630 --> 00:19:32,460
-Can't we get a break around here?
-<i>Code zero.</i>

259
00:19:32,550 --> 00:19:33,460
<i>Hit-and-run vehicle...</i>

260
00:19:33,550 --> 00:19:35,090
No wonder Chief Ki is sick.

261
00:19:35,590 --> 00:19:37,470
If he's out of commission,
who will take over?

262
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:39,510
Captain Eun?

263
00:19:40,510 --> 00:19:41,640
You can't do it, right?

264
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,810
I don't want Captain Eun
to be interim assistant chief.

265
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:49,520
He's a snob

266
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:52,320
and will be tough on our grades.

267
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,900
Is that all you can
worry about at this moment,

268
00:19:55,990 --> 00:19:57,320
you cold-hearted jerk?

269
00:19:59,910 --> 00:20:02,620
From where I stand, it's a big deal.
I'm being realistic.

270
00:20:04,450 --> 00:20:07,870
Jeez, you sure are realistic.

271
00:20:09,630 --> 00:20:10,590
Sang-su.

272
00:20:16,370 --> 00:20:19,080
they say you can survive being in
a lion's den, if you keep your cool.

273
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:22,290
If you're selfish enough to think of
yourself regardless of the situation,

274
00:20:22,370 --> 00:20:24,590
you'll surely have a great career
as a police officer.

275
00:20:25,710 --> 00:20:28,550
Yang-chon must have taught you well.

276
00:20:28,630 --> 00:20:29,670
Do you get private lessons?

277
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,050
Sir, I'm sorry!

278
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:36,100
I didn't mean it like that.

279
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:38,390
I'm truly sorry.

280
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,820
Why are you in the women's restroom?

281
00:20:56,580 --> 00:20:58,950
The chief, captain, and lieutenants
are holding at a meeting.

282
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:00,250
We're waiting here since

283
00:21:00,330 --> 00:21:01,710
the men's rest area and cafeteria

284
00:21:02,210 --> 00:21:03,540
are occupied by Team Two.

285
00:21:08,460 --> 00:21:09,710
So what's up

286
00:21:10,210 --> 00:21:11,170
with you two?

287
00:21:16,760 --> 00:21:18,180
Right, you broke up.

288
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:19,520
I knew that.

289
00:21:23,230 --> 00:21:24,850
This is a colossal mess.

290
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:28,360
Min-seok lives in a rental apartment
and pays 500,000 won for rent.

291
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:30,990
He's also taking care of his mom
who's suffering from cancer.

292
00:21:31,070 --> 00:21:32,820
Where would he get 50 million won?

293
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,610
Does his fiancee know?

294
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,700
No.

295
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:38,120
He's afraid that

296
00:21:38,580 --> 00:21:40,790
she'll call off the wedding
if she finds out.

297
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:42,200
Let's reveal everything in court.

298
00:21:42,710 --> 00:21:43,830
Just look at this.

299
00:21:44,210 --> 00:21:45,670
Anyone can see it's self-inflicted.

300
00:21:46,380 --> 00:21:48,840
Everyone here knows that.

301
00:21:49,420 --> 00:21:51,760
But how will we prove that
it was self-inflicted?

302
00:21:52,210 --> 00:21:54,550
A doctor's hands are tied
if a patient cries in pain.

303
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:57,390
Besides, it's a fact that Min-seok

304
00:21:57,470 --> 00:21:59,100
shoved this man.

305
00:21:59,180 --> 00:22:00,220
He had a reason to do so.

306
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:01,810
He hit another civilian, so--

307
00:22:01,890 --> 00:22:04,810
Does Internal Affairs care
about such circumstances?

308
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:06,850
All they care about is the manual.

309
00:22:06,940 --> 00:22:08,900
They'll ask why he pushed a civilian.

310
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:12,440
They'll only look at that one fact
and hound Min-seok about it.

311
00:22:13,610 --> 00:22:14,740
That's their job.

312
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,160
So, what are you thinking?

313
00:22:21,870 --> 00:22:23,580
-Let's go and kneel.
-Let's go and kneel.

314
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:25,870
What?

315
00:22:26,460 --> 00:22:28,130
We, cops, should kneel?

316
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:31,880
It's not fair, but we need to settle.

317
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:33,090
That's my conclusion.

318
00:22:33,170 --> 00:22:34,880
It'll get complicated
if Min-seok's charged.

319
00:22:35,510 --> 00:22:36,550
Settle it.

320
00:22:36,630 --> 00:22:39,760
We have to make the prosecutor
suspend the indictment.

321
00:22:39,850 --> 00:22:42,720
If this goes to court
and Min-seok gets probation,

322
00:22:43,220 --> 00:22:44,520
he'll have to leave the force.

323
00:22:45,310 --> 00:22:47,440
Even if this happened
while he was on duty,

324
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:49,860
if he's charged in civil
and criminal courts,

325
00:22:49,940 --> 00:22:52,230
Min-seok will have to find a lawyer

326
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:55,440
and prove his innocence all on his own.

327
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:57,780
He could get a suspended sentence.

328
00:22:57,860 --> 00:23:00,240
Even if his sentence is suspended,

329
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:03,450
Internal Affairs and
prosecutors will grill him.

330
00:23:05,080 --> 00:23:07,580
Dealing with all that will kill Min-seok
before anything happens.

331
00:23:08,460 --> 00:23:09,920
Something similar happened

332
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:13,340
to another cop who was investigated
and sued.

333
00:23:13,420 --> 00:23:15,340
He felt so insulted that
he killed himself.

334
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:17,720
A trial's too much.

335
00:23:18,510 --> 00:23:19,720
Do as I say.

336
00:23:20,260 --> 00:23:22,260
This is so upsetting.

337
00:23:22,850 --> 00:23:23,930
From our division,

338
00:23:24,890 --> 00:23:27,680
I'm one of the guys
who is older than the plaintiff so I'll--

339
00:23:27,770 --> 00:23:29,440
You stay out of it.

340
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:31,810
You want to get involved in everything.

341
00:23:34,570 --> 00:23:35,860
He's right.

342
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,820
You're our leader. Stay out of this one.

343
00:23:39,570 --> 00:23:42,320
So Sam-bo, Gyeong-mo and me.

344
00:23:42,450 --> 00:23:43,490
We'll meet the plaintiff

345
00:23:43,580 --> 00:23:45,490
and kneel and beg.

346
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:48,250
Let's get him to settle
for a lower amount.

347
00:23:48,830 --> 00:23:51,540
Once we reach a figure,
we can all pitch in.

348
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:54,420
Let's get the officers from
Min-seok's year to chip in too.

349
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,710
Yes, let's do that.

350
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:58,340
All we have are our fellow officers.

351
00:23:59,630 --> 00:24:02,140
That's it, then.
This issue has been dealt with.

352
00:24:02,220 --> 00:24:03,430
Now

353
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:05,810
let's talk about you, Boss.

354
00:24:07,390 --> 00:24:09,100
What are you doing to us?

355
00:24:09,180 --> 00:24:10,730
Gyeong-mo.

356
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:12,940
How could you make us

357
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:14,650
find out you're sick over the radio?

358
00:24:14,980 --> 00:24:16,440
Does that make sense?

359
00:24:33,630 --> 00:24:34,460
Okay.

360
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:37,920
About my condition.

361
00:24:39,590 --> 00:24:41,010
Neither the doctor nor I

362
00:24:41,840 --> 00:24:42,800
are sure of anything.

363
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:48,140
My doctor said there are many tumors,
but they're a mix of benign and malignant.

364
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,770
It could be stage one or stage three.

365
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:52,850
He can't say for sure right now.

366
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:54,900
He has to open me up

367
00:24:58,780 --> 00:24:59,690
to find out.

368
00:25:03,450 --> 00:25:05,200
So I suggested he do that.

369
00:25:07,830 --> 00:25:10,080
The surgery is before noon
the day after tomorrow.

370
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:13,040
I'll be admitted

371
00:25:14,290 --> 00:25:15,670
this afternoon.

372
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:22,630
I couldn't tell any of you

373
00:25:25,760 --> 00:25:27,600
for only one reason.

374
00:25:29,470 --> 00:25:30,640
It was

375
00:25:33,390 --> 00:25:35,650
because I felt sorry for
the one who'd have to fill in.

376
00:25:38,070 --> 00:25:39,070
Eun Gyeong-mo.

377
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,860
That would be you.

378
00:26:10,390 --> 00:26:11,220
Sam-bo.

379
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:16,560
You should go and see Hye-ri.

380
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:19,190
Go home

381
00:26:20,570 --> 00:26:21,820
and get some sleep first.

382
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:24,110
Go on.

383
00:26:26,570 --> 00:26:28,280
I know how you feel.

384
00:26:29,620 --> 00:26:31,120
Pray that my surgery goes well.

385
00:26:34,290 --> 00:26:35,500
I'll visit you.

386
00:26:50,930 --> 00:26:52,640
Yang-chon, you fool, Gyeong-mo--

387
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:54,310
I won't be disobedient.

388
00:26:55,980 --> 00:26:57,690
I'll serve him as I did you.

389
00:26:59,940 --> 00:27:01,150
Just focus on your surgery.

390
00:27:09,410 --> 00:27:10,570
Go.

391
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:14,200
Don't leave Jang-mi on her own
on a day like this.

392
00:27:17,830 --> 00:27:19,750
You know that cancer
is nothing these days, right?

393
00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:22,420
You'd better beat it.

394
00:27:27,170 --> 00:27:28,220
I will.

395
00:27:59,210 --> 00:28:00,670
Ki Han-sol

396
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:02,960
has colorectal cancer.

397
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:06,800
He doesn't know if
it's stage one or three.

398
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,170
They need to open up and see.

399
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:12,090
Don't bug him with your well wishes.

400
00:28:12,510 --> 00:28:13,720
-Just go home.
-Sir.

401
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:14,850
Shut your mouth.

402
00:28:15,890 --> 00:28:17,600
None of you

403
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,100
say anything.

404
00:28:20,560 --> 00:28:21,650
Don't say a thing

405
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,730
to me at all.

406
00:28:29,110 --> 00:28:30,150
Should we see the chief?

407
00:28:30,950 --> 00:28:34,490
No, let's listen to the captain.
Let's go home.

408
00:28:34,950 --> 00:28:36,080
Okay, let's go.

409
00:28:38,830 --> 00:28:41,040
They cure most cancers these days, right?

410
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:42,750
Yes, they do.

411
00:29:11,530 --> 00:29:12,860
Hey, where are you?

412
00:29:13,860 --> 00:29:16,780
<i>What worries you the most?</i>

413
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:20,160
Well...

414
00:29:22,540 --> 00:29:24,040
My weak wife.

415
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:27,170
<i>My newlywed daughter.</i>

416
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:33,930
<i>Will I be able to return to work?
Things like that.</i>

417
00:29:37,970 --> 00:29:39,310
As of this moment,

418
00:29:40,770 --> 00:29:41,810
be selfish.

419
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,100
<i>Put yourself first at all times.</i>

420
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:49,400
You got cancer for working
your butt off your whole life.

421
00:29:50,110 --> 00:29:53,150
Why are you worrying about others?

422
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:58,580
You need to survive
to care for your wife and daughter.

423
00:29:59,780 --> 00:30:00,830
<i>Without you,</i>

424
00:30:01,410 --> 00:30:03,750
<i>how could your wife,
daughter and we exist?</i>

425
00:30:05,710 --> 00:30:07,540
Don't worry about anyone else.

426
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,710
Starting right now,

427
00:30:11,130 --> 00:30:12,420
your health,

428
00:30:13,050 --> 00:30:14,420
your recovery.

429
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:17,640
That's all you should care about.

430
00:30:20,890 --> 00:30:21,970
<i>After the surgery,</i>

431
00:30:23,390 --> 00:30:24,640
<i>even if it's stage one,</i>

432
00:30:25,890 --> 00:30:27,900
don't you dare think about coming back to

433
00:30:28,650 --> 00:30:29,980
Hongil Patrol Division.

434
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:38,780
The police corporal position
at Bomun Station.

435
00:30:41,870 --> 00:30:44,200
Make sure you're the one
who ends up going. Not him.

436
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:46,290
Answer me.

437
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:50,840
Okay.

438
00:30:53,710 --> 00:30:54,970
You promised.

439
00:30:55,590 --> 00:30:59,180
-Now Ki Han-sol will--
<i>-Fine, I'll be selfish.</i>

440
00:31:00,430 --> 00:31:01,600
I'll put myself first.

441
00:31:02,350 --> 00:31:03,350
I will survive.

442
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:05,980
<i>I'll live, not die.</i>

443
00:31:07,190 --> 00:31:08,900
<i>Forget about my wife,</i>

444
00:31:08,980 --> 00:31:10,940
daughter, loyal officers.

445
00:31:12,020 --> 00:31:13,230
I'll think of myself first.

446
00:31:18,780 --> 00:31:19,950
I hope

447
00:31:21,450 --> 00:31:22,910
the surgery goes well.

448
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,250
Thanks.

449
00:31:29,330 --> 00:31:31,330
You fool. We aren't strangers.

450
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:01,910
WIFE

451
00:32:06,700 --> 00:32:09,410
WIFE

452
00:32:11,210 --> 00:32:13,540
Goodness, it's my wife.

453
00:32:18,090 --> 00:32:19,300
Our daughter must've told you.

454
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:24,300
Gosh, don't cry.
I'll be fine after the surgery.

455
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:29,430
You see,

456
00:32:29,520 --> 00:32:31,520
this is exactly why I couldn't tell you.

457
00:32:32,810 --> 00:32:34,480
This is why I've kept it from you.

458
00:32:37,780 --> 00:32:40,030
Enough already. I'm not dying, okay?

459
00:32:40,110 --> 00:32:41,320
Stop crying already.

460
00:32:46,410 --> 00:32:47,490
I told you to stop crying.

461
00:33:05,100 --> 00:33:06,220
Dad, are you back for good?

462
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:07,970
No.

463
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:11,390
You're so annoying.
Just move back already.

464
00:33:13,060 --> 00:33:14,150
You brat.

465
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:17,110
Aren't you happier without my nagging?

466
00:33:17,270 --> 00:33:19,070
You're just saying that, right?

467
00:33:27,490 --> 00:33:28,660
I'm so annoyed.

468
00:33:29,410 --> 00:33:30,540
What's annoying you?

469
00:33:31,120 --> 00:33:33,210
You'd better not tell me
to work hard from now on.

470
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,540
-What?
-Aren't I right?

471
00:33:37,170 --> 00:33:39,880
What good comes out of working hard?
Look at you and Mom.

472
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:43,970
Let's be honest.

473
00:33:44,050 --> 00:33:46,090
You two are probably the most honest cops,

474
00:33:47,010 --> 00:33:50,220
but the force reprimanded you severely
instead of rewarding you.

475
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:52,770
It's so crazy.

476
00:33:53,730 --> 00:33:54,560
"Reprimanded"?

477
00:33:55,690 --> 00:33:56,560
Haven't you heard?

478
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,190
Ask Mom about it, then.

479
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:11,240
Why did you call? What's up?

480
00:34:15,540 --> 00:34:17,500
Why aren't you saying anything?
You called me.

481
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:20,380
<i>We heard that the police
didn't look into the case</i>

482
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:22,960
<i>immediately after receiving a call
about it. Why did it happen?</i>

483
00:34:23,050 --> 00:34:24,760
<i>You must be watching the news about me.</i>

484
00:34:25,510 --> 00:34:27,010
That's so annoying.

485
00:34:28,010 --> 00:34:31,100
Why are they showing that over and over?

486
00:34:31,640 --> 00:34:33,560
-Don't watch it.
<i>-The chief just said</i>

487
00:34:33,640 --> 00:34:35,850
<i>that he'll severely reprimand
who was in charge.</i>

488
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:37,480
<i>Captain, what's your thought on it?</i>

489
00:34:37,560 --> 00:34:39,400
<i>Father,
I'm not trying to give you an excuse.</i>

490
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:42,150
-<i>I really didn't do anything wrong.
-The police failed to...</i>

491
00:34:42,230 --> 00:34:43,570
I already know that.

492
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:46,200
You'd never do anything wrong.

493
00:34:46,700 --> 00:34:48,410
You always do a good job no matter what.

494
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:52,040
I'm okay.

495
00:34:53,370 --> 00:34:54,910
I won't be discouraged by this.

496
00:34:56,500 --> 00:34:59,750
I'm a little upset, but I'll be fine soon.

497
00:35:00,630 --> 00:35:02,250
<i>Everyone in the country is enraged by...</i>

498
00:35:02,340 --> 00:35:06,130
<i>You probably called to console me,
but you don't know what to say, right?</i>

499
00:35:06,590 --> 00:35:08,130
<i>Since you've never done it before.</i>

500
00:35:09,220 --> 00:35:11,550
-You're right.
-<i>The police's abuse of power...</i>

501
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:13,350
<i>Just the fact that you called is enough.</i>

502
00:35:14,470 --> 00:35:16,890
Thanks. You made me feel better.

503
00:35:19,310 --> 00:35:21,650
Yang-chon is here.
I'll pass the phone to him.

504
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,070
Dad, I can't come home.

505
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,450
I'll get some sleep here and--

506
00:35:31,740 --> 00:35:33,450
<i>There's nothing here but this old man.</i>

507
00:35:33,540 --> 00:35:36,040
Why would you even come here?

508
00:35:36,160 --> 00:35:37,160
Just live there.

509
00:35:38,210 --> 00:35:39,420
<i>A complaint has been submitted.</i>

510
00:35:40,170 --> 00:35:44,050
<i>The police and the prosecution are
currently locking horns with each other</i>

511
00:35:44,250 --> 00:35:47,220
<i>over investigative powers surrounding...</i>

512
00:35:50,510 --> 00:35:51,890
Those bastards.

513
00:36:11,410 --> 00:36:12,530
Why are you drinking?

514
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:13,740
I'm off today,

515
00:36:14,450 --> 00:36:15,620
but don't you have to work?

516
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,370
They told me to take a break.

517
00:36:20,540 --> 00:36:23,210
-I've been suspended.
-You got suspended, not a pay cut?

518
00:36:23,290 --> 00:36:24,960
They obviously can't stand me.

